<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="425" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="425">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="425">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Thomson &amp; Holzenthal" authorityYear="2015" class="Insecta" family="Hydroptilidae" genus="Leucotrichia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Leucotrichia rhomba" order="Trichoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="425" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rhomba">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="425">Leucotrichia rhomba</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is similar to 
<taxonomicName genus="L." lsidName="L. brochophora" pageId="0" pageNumber="425" rank="species" species="brochophora">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="425">L. brochophora</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Flint, 1991 and 
<taxonomicName genus="L." lsidName="L. padera" pageId="0" pageNumber="425" rank="species" species="padera">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="425">L. padera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Flint, 1991, two species recorded from Colombia, but not currently known from Panama. All three species share a similar appearance of the phallus apex, with no spines and either few or no externally sclerotized structures. The anterolateral margin of segment IX is also produced in all three species. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Thomson &amp; Holzenthal" authorityYear="2015" class="Insecta" family="Hydroptilidae" genus="Leucotrichia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Leucotrichia rhomba" order="Trichoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="425" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rhomba">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="425">Leucotrichia rhomba</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be recognized by the elongate mesoventral process of segment VII, which is enlarged, rhomboid, and rugose in ventral view (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 13" captionStartId="F13" captionText="Figure 13. Leucotrichia rhomba Thomson &amp; Holzenthal, 2015. Male genitalia: A segments VII-X, lateral B segments VII-IX, ventral C segments VII-X, dorsal D phallus, lateral E phallus, dorsal. Modified from Harris and Armitage (2019)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1111.77371.figure13" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/713501" pageId="0" pageNumber="425">13A, B</figureCitation>
), and by the obovoid dorsal sclerite of the phallus apex (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 13" captionStartId="F13" captionText="Figure 13. Leucotrichia rhomba Thomson &amp; Holzenthal, 2015. Male genitalia: A segments VII-X, lateral B segments VII-IX, ventral C segments VII-X, dorsal D phallus, lateral E phallus, dorsal. Modified from Harris and Armitage (2019)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1111.77371.figure13" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/713501" pageId="0" pageNumber="425">13E</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<caption doi="10.3897/zookeys.1111.77371.figure13" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/713501" pageId="0" pageNumber="425" start="Figure 13" startId="F13">
