<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="425" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="425">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="425">
The drawings of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Thomson &amp; Holzenthal" authorityYear="2015" class="Insecta" family="Hydroptilidae" genus="Leucotrichia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Leucotrichia rhomba" order="Trichoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="425" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rhomba">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="425">Leucotrichia rhomba</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in 
<bibRefCitation author="Harris, SC" journalOrPublisher="Insecta Mundi" pageId="0" pageNumber="425" pagination="1 - 54" refId="B13" refString="Harris, SC, Armitage, BJ, 2019. The Trichoptera of Panama. X. The Quebrada Rambala Drainage, with description of 19 new species of microcaddisfies (Trichoptera: Hydroptilidae). Insecta Mundi 0707: 1 - 54" title="The Trichoptera of Panama. X. The Quebrada Rambala Drainage, with description of 19 new species of microcaddisfies (Trichoptera: Hydroptilidae)." volume="0707" year="2019">Harris and Armitage (2019)</bibRefCitation>
emphasize the apical phallic sclerite which is somewhat oval in shape. In 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.3897/zookeys.499.8360" author="Thomson, RE" journalOrPublisher="ZooKeys" pageId="0" pageNumber="425" pagination="1 - 100" refId="B30" refString="Thomson, RE, Holzenthal, RW, 2015. A revision of the Neotropical caddisfly genus Leucotrichia Mosely, 1934 (Hydroptilidae: Leucotrichiinae). ZooKeys 499: 1 - 100, DOI: https://doi.org/10.3897/zookeys.499.8360" title="A revision of the Neotropical caddisfly genus Leucotrichia Mosely, 1934 (Hydroptilidae: Leucotrichiinae)." url="https://doi.org/10.3897/zookeys.499.8360" volume="499" year="2015">Thomson and Holzenthal (2015)</bibRefCitation>
this sclerite is not emphasized, rather they use the basal sclerites. In 
<bibRefCitation author="Harris, SC" journalOrPublisher="Insecta Mundi" pageId="0" pageNumber="425" pagination="1 - 54" refId="B13" refString="Harris, SC, Armitage, BJ, 2019. The Trichoptera of Panama. X. The Quebrada Rambala Drainage, with description of 19 new species of microcaddisfies (Trichoptera: Hydroptilidae). Insecta Mundi 0707: 1 - 54" title="The Trichoptera of Panama. X. The Quebrada Rambala Drainage, with description of 19 new species of microcaddisfies (Trichoptera: Hydroptilidae)." volume="0707" year="2019">Harris and Armitage (2019)</bibRefCitation>
, these basal sclerites are indicated, but secondarily to the apical sclerite. In examining material from Panama, the apical sclerite proved to be the best character for identifying the species. The other genitalic features are similarly drawn in these two papers. The minor difference in figures could be attributed to artistic interpretation of taxonomic features.
</paragraph>
